<h3>What is Asian Century</h3>
<ul>
<li>Phrase said to have arisen in 1988 meeting btw <strong>Deng Xiaoping </strong>and <strong>Rajiv Gandhi</strong> re-establishing relations after 1962 war</li>
<li>Refers to the <strong>dominant role that Asia is expected to play in the 21st century</strong> due to its burgeoning economy and demographic trends.</li>
<li>The growth potential of Asia- Region with max growth potential</li></ul>
<h3>Why Asian Century</h3>
<p style="margin-left:40px"><br />
• Demographics&nbsp;<br />
• Exploring an<strong> international block-chain currency</strong> for digital settlements without relying on the dollar</p>
<p style="margin-left:40px">• <strong>Construction Projects </strong>– Infra companies backed by Asian banks internationalising Asian currency like Renminbi.<br />
• <strong>Culture</strong> – Languages, films, Yoga etc. are part of Asian culture and it led to more aware culture of world.<br />
• Global growth generators –&nbsp; Asian countries are creating more growth for world by increasing trade, investment and large markets for products.<br />
• Global Institutions –Need Multilateralism</p>
<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Geo Political Significance of Mammallapuram&nbsp;Summit 2019</h3>
<ul>
<li>Evidence of Increasingly "Multipolar" century</li>
<li>Sharing of power btw many (Economic+Political)</li>
<li>No single country to dictate global world order or challenges</li>
<li><strong>ASIA TO BE THE CENTRE OF THIS DEVELOPMENT-&nbsp;</strong>Potential to take over other regions (Economically) Thus "Asian Century"</li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Growing significance of Asia?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Asian economy to become &gt; ROW&nbsp;</strong>
<ul>
<li>The combined PPP of Asia &gt; ROW in near future</li>
<li>1st time since 19th century</li></ul></li>
<li>Asia- more integrated- eg RCEP , AIIB</li>
<li>Constructive force for Global Governance (China and India act as forces to for multilateralism)</li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What role can India-China play ?</h3>
<ul>
<li>I-C Largest economies in Asia</li>
<li>Promote a fair and inclusive globalisation</li>
<li>Population (35% of world population); Man power or Human resource</li>
<li>GDP Together of I-C 45% of global growth</li>
<li>Reforms in Multilateral Institution lack a leadership as of now</li>
<li>Can help in regional stability</li></ul>